es.us.isa.aml.translator.builders.wsag.model

Class GuaranteeTerm

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.us.isa.aml.translator.builders.wsag.model.GuaranteeTerm

  • public class GuaranteeTerm
extends java.lang.Object
    One motivation for creating a service agreement between a service provider and a service consumer is to provide assurance to the service consumer on the service quality and/or resource availability offered by the service provider. Guarantee terms define this assurance on service quality, associated with the service described by the service definition terms.
    Author:
    jdelafuente

    • Field Detail

      • name

        private java.lang.String name
        The MANDATORY name attribute (of type String) represents the name given to a guarantee. Since an Agreement MAY encompass multiple GuaranteeTerms each term SHOULD be given a unique name.

      • obligated

        private ServiceRole obligated
        This attribute defines, which party enters the obligation to the guarantee term. The ServiceRole can be either ServiceConsumer or ServiceProvider.

      • serviceScope

        private ServiceScope serviceScope
        A guarantee term can have one or more service scopes. A service scope describes to what service element specifically a guarantee term applies. For example, a performance guarantee might only apply to one operation of a Web service at a particular end point. If a guarantee term applies to multiple services, a set of service scopes MUST be defined.

      • qualifyingCondition

        private QualifyingCondition qualifyingCondition
        This element MAY appear in order to express a precondition under which a guarantee holds.

      • slo

        private ServiceLevelObjective slo
        This element expresses the condition that must be met to satisfy the guarantee.

      • bvl

        private BusinessValueList bvl
        This is the higher level element that contains a list of business value elements associated with a service level objective.
